Data availability

            Country-level crop yield statistics were obtained from the FAO’s FAOSTAT database (https://www.fao.org/faostat/en/), while irrigated area fractions were derived from FAO’s AQUASTAT global water and agriculture information system (https://www.fao.org/aquastat/en/). Spatial irrigation patterns were derived from the MIRCA2000 dataset, which provides global monthly irrigated and rainfed crop areas (https://www.uni-frankfurt.de/45218031/MIRCA). Climate conditions during crop growth were characterized by ERA5 reanalysis from the European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts, which provides global climate data at 0.25° × 0.25° resolution from 1980 to 2020 (https://cds.climate.copernicus.eu/datasets/reanalysis-era5-single-levels?tab=overview). Crop yields under future warming scenarios of 1.5 °C and 3 °C above pre-industrial levels (1850–1900) were projected using climate data from CMIP6, as provided by ISIMIP (https://www.isimip.org/outputdata/). Source data are provided with this paper.
          Code availability

            All statistical analyses were conducted in Python (version 3.7.16) using the statsmodels package (version 0.13.5), while the GAM analysis with thin-plate splines were conducted in R (version 4.3.0) using the mgcv package (version 1.8-42). The results and code are available via Zenodo at https://zenodo.org/records/11069417 (ref. 96).
